},
"20": {
&"character": "Musician",
&"id": "20",
&"next_id": "21",
&"text": "The songs can make wonderful things happen... make items or creatures appear, or even open portals to other regions of Threadbare.",
&"type": "dialogue"
},
"21": {
&"character": "Musician",
&"id": "21",
&"next_id": "22",
&"text": "Those altars? They hold the memory of each song in the ashes of their fires.",
&"type": "dialogue"
},
"22": {
&"character": "Musician",
&"id": "22",
&"next_id": "23",
&"text": "Now, if I remember correctly, there's a song that used to open the portal to the Ink Well, where songwriters found the ink to write all the songs of the world.",
&"type": "dialogue"
},
"23": {
&"character": "Musician",
&"id": "23",
&"next_id": "24",
&"text": "Let's see if I can remember how it works...",
&"type": "dialogue"
},
"24": {
&"character": "Musician",
&"id": "24",
&"next_id": "25",
&"text": "Try tapping the first, and second stones, then check the first altar above. If you see flames, we're on to the right melody.",
&"type": "dialogue"
},
